==Latin==
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} [[δράκων]], a "[[dragon]]"

===Noun===
'''dracō''' (genitive: '''[[draconis|dracōnis]]'''); {{m}}, ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|third declension]]''
(feminine: [[dracaena]], diminutive: [[dracunculus]])

# A [[dragon]]; a kind of [[serpent]].
# The constellation [[Draco]].
# (''ecclesiastic''): The [[Devil]].

